= Inline Styles

Inline styles allow you to apply custom CSS classes and styling to text.

== Basic Inline Style

This paragraph contains [.highlight]#highlighted text#.

== Inline Style with Class

This paragraph has [.important]#important text#.

This paragraph has [.warning]#warning text#.

== Inline Style with ID

This paragraph has [#unique-id]#text with ID#.

== Inline Style with Multiple Classes

This paragraph has [.class1.class2]#text with multiple classes#.

== Inline Style with Formatting

This paragraph has [.highlight]#highlighted# and *bold* text.

This paragraph has [.important]#important# and _italic_ text.

== Inline Style in Lists

* Item with [.highlight]#highlighted# text
* Regular item
* Another item with [.warning]#warning# text

== Inline Style with Links

Check the [.important]#important section# at https://example.com[here].

== Inline Style Examples

[.user-input]#Type your name here#

[.code]#function example() {}#

[.error]#Error: Something went wrong#

[.success]#Success: Operation completed#

== Inline Style at Boundaries

[.highlight]#Highlighted at start# of paragraph.

[.highlight]#Highlighted at end# of paragraph.

